                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d788">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–1147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spiker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-11T09:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 11, 1947—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 10—11:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Refer mytel 103 to Embassy, 77 to Department Sept. 5. ComNavWesPac informs me
                    pilot returned to Navy yesterday eve result of negotiations at Goose Point.
                    Assume Embassy has kept Department advised of interim ComNavWesPac reports
                    September 6 and 9 through <hi rend="smallcaps">Alusna</hi>, Nanking. Details
                    will be reported when available.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking as 108, repeated Department as 82.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spiker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
